The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA) and proposes a new benchmark for evaluating explainable and high-order visual question reasoning ability. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image scene graphs and commonsense knowledge bases, indicating a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a new knowledge-routed modular network (KM-net), which suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
